    "extras": [
      "June to September works especially well for this route: Cape Town stays cool but clear enough for scenery, while Kruger’s dry season usually improves wildlife spotting around water sources.",
      "Robben Island ferries often sell out well in advance, so book that slot before finalizing the rest of your Cape Town days.",
      "Vodacom is the most dependable SIM choice if Kruger is a priority; city speeds are good, but mobile data becomes patchier once you are deep inside the park.",
      "Baz Bus is useful if you want the Garden Route without self-driving, but a rental car gives you far more flexibility for Cape Peninsula viewpoints and Tsitsikamma stops.",
      "Durban is the easiest South African stop for vegetarian Indian travelers thanks to Raj’s Vegetarian, curry houses, and Victoria Street Market food stalls.",
      "Keep big-city nights simple: stay in well-rated tourist districts such as City Bowl, Sandton, Rosebank, or Umhlanga and use ride-hailing instead of long late walks."
    ],
